f128::<impl f128>::abs.doc:
Computes the absolute value of `self`.

This function always returns the precise result.

# Examples

```
#![feature(f128)]
# #[cfg(all(target_arch = "x86_64", target_os = "linux"))] {

let x = 3.5_f128;
let y = -3.5_f128;

assert_eq!(x.abs(), x);
assert_eq!(y.abs(), -y);

assert!(f128::NAN.abs().is_nan());
# }
```

